## State Management Standards
- Use `useState` for component-level state
- Use `useEffect` for side effects and data fetching
- Use `useParams` and `useNavigate` from React Router
- Always set loading states before API calls
- Error handling with try-catch and message notifications

## API Integration Standards
- API calls in useEffect with dependencies array
- Error messages: `error.response?.data?.error?.message || 'Fallback message'`
- Loading states: Show skeleton or spinner
- Success messages: Use `message.success()`
- Show toasts for user feedback

## Form & Input Standards
- Input components from Ant Design
- Text areas with proper height and styling
- Labels above inputs in gray text
- Helper text for context
- Validation on submit

## Modal Standards
- Title with icon for context
- Footer with Cancel and Action buttons
- Proper styling matching button standards
- Confirmation messages before destructive actions
- Width: `600px` to `900px` depending on content

## Table Standards (if used)
- Sortable columns
- Pagination with proper page size
- Filtering options in header
- Row actions
- Responsive design with overflow handling

## Accessibility Standards
- Alt text for images
- ARIA labels where needed
- Keyboard navigation support
- Color contrasts meeting WCAG AA
- Focus states on interactive elements

